data.description:
This task is rather simple: Generate a random maze of dimensions width x height.

The maze should be a width x height matrix (array of arrays):

* Each cell must be an object having an x,y (row/column). 

* Every cell in the maze must have at least one path to any other cell (No unreachable cells exist).

* Each cell must have have an opening in one or more of the following direction: North, South, East and West. Eg. a cell A connected to its right neighbor B will have A.east = B (and B.west = A).

* The border may contain no "exits" - that is, the border should be unbroken.

* All rows (in the matrix) should be of the same length.

* Width and height arguments are always legal and at least 2.

* Two maze of same dimensions should be different - but in the rare circumstances where Math.random gives similar results. 

A simple 2 x 2 maze is generated through:

```javascript
var maze = [[{x:0,y:0},{x:1,y:0}],[{x:0,y:1},{x:1,y:1}]];
maze.cell = function(x,y){return this[y][x]};
maze[0][0].south = maze.cell(0,1);
maze[0][0].east = maze.cell(1,0);
maze[0][1].west = maze.cell(0,0);
maze[1][0].north = maze.cell(0,0);
maze[1][0].east = maze.cell(1,1);
maze[1][1].west = maze.cell(0,1);
```

Your solution will be tested with random starting and end points.

A few helper functions are provided:

checkMaze(maze) - Run a few path checks on the given maze.

display(maze) - Returns a string depicting the maze. 

stringify(maze) - Generate a string containing a piece of JavaScript code representing the given maze. This was used to generate the example 'maze' above.
